The world of fact is outrunning the world of fiction."
Ghosh believes old legends have a lot to teach us about how to think about the cataclysmic effects of climate change.
"Fiction allows us to look at the world in a different way," he says.
Ghosh often sets his own fiction at the blurry boundary between land and water.